*New case* : a person with TB disease who has never been treated for TB or has only ever taken TB drugs for less than 1 month.

 *Recurrent case* : A person with TB disease who has previously been treated for TB, was declared cured or treatment completed at the end of their most recent course of T treatment and is now diagnosed with a new episode of TB. (Previously referred to as relapse).

 *Re-registered case* : A person with TB disease who has been notified previously as a TB case, who started treatment and took TB drugs for at least 1 month but who was not declared cured of treatment completed, and is now being started on a new course of TB treatment. (Previously referred to as retreatment).

 *New episode of TB:* New or recurrent case. (Previously referred to as new or relapse). New episodes of TB are considered incident TB cases.

 *Previously treated case* : Recurrent or re-registered case.

dashboardItems.text:
*TB04.1: Rifampicin-resistant TB (RR-TB)*
Rifampicin-resistant TB (RR-TB) is a person who has TB that is resistant to at least rifampicin, with or without resistance to other TB drugs.

*TB04.2: Multidrug-resistant TB (MDR-TB)*
Multidrug-resistant TB (MDR-TB) is a patient who has RR-TB with resistance to isoniazid.

*TB04.3: Isoniazid-resistant, rifampicin-susceptible TB (Hr-TB)* 
Isoniazid-resistant, rifampicin-susceptible TB (Hr-TB) is a patient who has TB that is resistant to isoniazid but susceptible to rifampicin.

*TB04.4: Pre-extensively drug-resistant TB in RR-TB (pre-XDR-TB)*
 Pre-extensively drug-resistant TB (pre-XDR-TB) is a patient who has TB that is resistant to rifampicin (RR-TB) and also resistant to at least one fluoroquinolone (either levofloxacin or moxifloxacin).

*TB04.5: Extensively drug-resistant TB in RR-TB (XDR-TB)*
Extensively-drug resistant TB (XDR-TB) is a patient who has TB that is resistant to rifampicin and resistant to least one fluoroquinolone (pre-XDR-TB) and least one other “Group A” drug (bedaquiline or linezolid).

dashboardItems.text:
*TB05.2: Treatment outcomes - Quarterly*
* Treatment outcomes for regimens designed to treat RIF-susceptible TB and short regimens designed to treat RR-TB are for the patients registered in the same quarter one year prior.
* Treatment outcomes for long regimens designed to treat RR-TB are for the patients registered in the same quarter two years prior.

*TB06.2: Treatment outcomes*

Treatment outcomes for regimens designed to treat RIF-susceptible TB and short regimens designed to treat RR-TB are for the patients registered one year prior.

Treatment outcomes for long regimens designed to treat RR-TB are for the patients registered two years prior.

*TB06.3: Case outcomes*
Case outcomes include the outcomes for people who did not start treatment and the treatment outcomes for patients who started any regimen to treat TB. They are for the patients registered two years prior.
